---
import en from '../../i18n/en';
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';

const toc = [
  { id: 'scope', label: '1. Scope' },
  { id: 'incoming', label: '2. Incoming complaints' },
  { id: 'outgoing', label: '3. Outgoing notices (DMCA)' },
  { id: 'counter', label: '4. Counter-notice' },
  { id: 'contact', label: '5. Contact' },
];
---
<LegalLayout t={en} lang="en" pageTitle="DMCA / Takedown" tocItems={toc}>
  <p class="meta">Last updated: 2 May 2026 - Version 1.0</p>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>In short:</strong> PluriFin respects third-party intellectual property and expects the
    same in return. To report infringing material related to us, or to report unauthorised use of
    PluriFin content, write to
    <a href="mailto:plurifin.app+legal@gmail.com">plurifin.app+legal@gmail.com</a>.
  </div>

  <h2 id="scope">1. Scope</h2>
  <p>This page summarises the procedure to report copyright or trademark infringements related to
  the Portfolio Manager app, the PluriFin website and related content. For the full templates (in
  Italian and English) refer to the long-form document published at
  <a href="/legal/en/dmca.html">/legal/en/dmca.html</a>.</p>

  <h2 id="incoming">2. Incoming complaints</h2>
  <p>If you believe content published by PluriFin (marketing site, screenshots, blog, open-source
  code) infringes your rights, send a notice that includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Identification of the infringing material (full URLs, screenshots).</li>
    <li>Identification of the protected work you own (registration, first publication).</li>
    <li>Statutory references (DMCA 17 U.S.C. par. 512 or EU Directive 2019/790).</li>
    <li>A signed good-faith and accuracy statement.</li>
    <li>Complete contact details and an ID copy (on request).</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Typical response time: 5 business days. On clearly grounded reports we remove or replace the
  material before responding.</p>

  <h2 id="outgoing">3. Outgoing notices (DMCA)</h2>
  <p>When PluriFin identifies an abusive copy, a commercial fork or a trademark violation, we file a
  formal notice with the hosting platform. The US platforms most often used are GitHub
  (<a href="https://github.com/contact/dmca">github.com/contact/dmca</a>), Google Play
  (<a href="https://support.google.com/legal/answer/3463191">support.google.com/legal</a>),
  Cloudflare and AWS. For EU hosts, a cease-and-desist is sent under D.Lgs. 70/2003 art. 17.</p>
  <p>Action threshold: we act only on clear and material violations (app clones, full site copies,
  commercial code forks). We do not act on criticism, reviews or screenshots in press articles --
  these fall under fair use.</p>

  <h2 id="counter">4. Counter-notice</h2>
  <p>If PluriFin content is removed following a notice we consider unfounded or erroneous, we file a
  DMCA counter-notice (17 U.S.C. par. 512(g)) asserting good-faith belief in the misidentification,
  accepting US jurisdiction for cross-border cases and requesting restoration of the material.</p>

  <h2 id="contact">5. Contact</h2>
  <p>Dedicated legal email: <a href="mailto:plurifin.app+legal@gmail.com">plurifin.app+legal@gmail.com</a></p>
  <p>Replies within 5-10 business days. For urgent matters mark the subject with "URGENT DMCA".</p>

  <hr />
  <div class="note">
    This document is an operational summary. For the full template texts (Italian and English) and
    internal handling procedures, refer to the long-form legal document at
    <a href="/legal/en/dmca.html">/legal/en/dmca.html</a>.
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
